727632f-a.title: Queens: Northern Boulevard - Douglaston Parkway
727632f-a.text:
Northern Boulevard, north side, between Douglaston Parkway (left), and 244th Street (right) showina the 2ion Church (P.E.) of Douglaston. This church was donated by Wynant Van 2andt Jr. He also gave the pipe organ and other furniture. The church was constructed on July 30, 1830. Bishop Hobart was the rector. Wm. P. Douglas donated the Chancel. The Parish Hall was larcely built by a cift of Bloodcood Cutler, the Long Island farmer poet. This edifice was damaged by fire on December 24, 1924. The new edifice was
opened about January 1st, 1926.
June 1922.
Eumene L. Armbruster Collection.

Northern Boulevard, north side, between Douglaston Parkway (left) and 244th Street (right), showing the Erotestant Episcopal 2ion Church of Douglaston. For a complete history see other views. This is a set of three views taken at the same time but from different angles.
